Class BulkInvoiceItem

java.lang.Object
com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase
entity.BulkInvoiceItem
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.guidewire.commons.entity.Keyable, com.guidewire.commons.entity.Sourceable, com.guidewire.pl.persistence.core.BeanMethods, Editable, KeyableBean, Retireable, Versionable, BulkInvoiceItemMethods, Bean, BundleProvider, Comparable<Bean>
@Generated(value="com.guidewire.pl.metadata.codegen.Codegen", comments="BulkInvoiceItem.eti;BulkInvoiceItem.eix;BulkInvoiceItem.etx") public class BulkInvoiceItem extends com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase implements Retireable, BulkInvoiceItemMethods
BulkInvoiceItem Describes one item of the BulkInvoice, and corresponds to one line item of the original invoice. It contains data fields that define the reserve line to which the item is to be coded, as well as the amount and the PaymentType.

    • getPublicID

      public String getPublicID()
      The external ID for this entity.

      PublicID values are automatically created during the commit, if not previously set. The format is random, meeting security requirements based on current industry standards. For example:

      • pc:SYinDB2XTOgNZFs1NpxU8
      • pc:Sf8QS4N5RBS-h8_pj-Oy_
      • pc:SBwBzylneecSNr6_Ub4IO
      Your configuration code must not assume any particular format for PublicID values, in either the prefix or body portion of the string, or even assume the existence of a prefix. Do not make any assumptions at all about the content of a PublicID value, including expectations that values are sequential, numeric, or prefixed.

      You can subclass and override AbstractBundleTransactionCallback.afterSetIds(gw.pl.persistence.core.Bundle) if you need to see the value in the same commit. 

      
  var note = new Note(bundle)
  bundle.addBundleTransactionCallback(new AbstractBundleTransactionCallback() {
     override function afterSetIds(b : Bundle) {
       log.info("Created Note " + note.PublicID)
     }
  })
      Specified by:

    • isEditable

      public boolean isEditable()
      Tests whether this BulkInvoiceItem is editable. It is editable if:

      • The status is one of:
        1. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_DRAFT
        2. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_NOTVALID
      or
      • The status of the owning Bulk Invoice is BulkInvoiceStatus.TC_AWAITINGSUBMISSION and the status of this item is one of:
        1. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_APPROVED
        2. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_REJECTED
        3. invalid reference 
          BulkInvoiceItemStatus#TC_INREVIEW

      Returns:
      true if this BulkInvoiceItem is editable, else false

Calling this method will force the bean to be written to the database and participate fully in the commit cycle e.g. pre-update rules will be run, etc.
